org.chronos.chronodb.internal.api

Interface ChronoDBInternal

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.AutoCloseable, ChronoDB, Lockable, TransactionSource
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractChronoDB, ChunkedChronoDB, InMemoryChronoDB, JdbcChronoDB, MapDBChronoDB, TuplChronoDB

    public interface ChronoDBInternal
extends ChronoDB, Lockable
    An interface that defines methods on ChronoDB for internal use.

    If you down-cast a ChronoDB to a ChronoDBInternal, you leave the area of the public API, which is strongly discouraged!

      • entryStream

        CloseableIterator<ChronoDBEntry> entryStream()
        Creates an iterable stream of entries that reside in this ChronoDB instance.

        IMPORTANT: The resulting stream must be closed by the caller!

        Recommended usage pattern is with "try-with-resources": 

         try (ChronoDBEntryStream stream = chronoDBInternal.entryStream()) {
        while (stream.hasNext()) {
                ChronoDBEntry entry = stream.next();
                // do something with the entry
        }
 } catch (Exception e) {
        // treat exception
 }
        Returns:
        The stream of entries. Never null, may be empty. Must be closed explicitly.

      • loadEntries

        void loadEntries(java.util.List<ChronoDBEntry> entries)
        Loads the given list of entries into this ChronoDB instance.

        Please note that it is assumed that the corresponding branches already exist in the system. This method performs no locking on its own!

        Parameters:
        entries - The entries to load. Must not be null, may be empty.
